# EVE Online industry (domain context)

This repo is **EVE Industry Organizer**: a frontend-only React app for EVE Online manufacturing planning. No EVE SSO login; users enter characters, skills, and BPOs manually. Prices come from public APIs; static game data from the SDE.

## Game basics

- **EVE Online**: sci-fi MMO with a player-driven economy. Currency is **ISK**.
- **Manufacturing**: use a **BPO** (blueprint original) at a station to turn inputs into outputs over time.
- **Runs**: one job produces `productQuantity Ã— runs` items. This app defaults to batch runs of 100 (`batchSize`).
- **ME** (Material Efficiency, 0â€“10): reduces input materials by 1% per level.
- **TE** (Time Efficiency, 0â€“20): reduces job duration by 4% per level.
- **Research**: ME/TE are raised via copy-time research jobs (tracked as timers in user data).

## Blueprint data (this app)

Static data is split:

| File | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `public/data/blueprints.json` | Full manufacturing BPO registry: recipes, `tier`, `spaceClass`, `productGroup` |
| `public/data/catalog.json` | Per-hub profit rankings (product type IDs only), nested by `spaceClass` then `tier` |

## Blueprint tiers (`tier`)

| Value | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `t1` | Tech I, Tech III, structures, abyssal, etc. (default meta groups) |
| `t2` | Tech II (SDE meta group 2) |
| `faction` | Storyline, faction, officer, deadspace meta groups |

## Security space (`spaceClass`)

| Value | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `highsec` | Default trade-hub manufacturing |
| `lowsec` | e.g. structures with `anchoringSecurityLevelMax` below 0.45 |
| `nullsec` | Sov structures, officer/deadspace meta, no-market items (non-WH) |
| `wormhole` | Sleeper/T3/WH groups; no-market WH heuristics |

Classification rules live in `scripts/lib/blueprint-groups.mjs`. Rankings use spot profit in `scripts/fetch-sde-data.mjs` / `rebuild-catalog.mjs`.

## Cost & profit (match `src/lib/cost.ts`)

- **Material cost**: sum of (quantity Ã— hub price) after ME is applied.
- **Job cost (NPC station)**: `materialCost Ã— systemCostIndex`. Cost index comes from ESI `industry/systems`.
- **Capital** = material cost + job cost.
- **Revenue**: sell price Ã— output qty, minus broker fee and sales tax (defaults 1% / 3.6%).
- **Spot profit** (rankings only): raw SDE materials, no ME/TE, for fast catalog precompute in `scripts/fetch-sde-data.mjs`.
- **Advanced Industry** skill: 3% time reduction per level (used in TE calc).

Do not invent different ME/TE formulas unless fixing a known game-mechanics bug.

## Trade hubs

Five hubs: **Jita**, **Amarr**, **Dodixie**, **Rens**, **Hek** (`HubId` in `src/types/index.ts`). Each hub has a sell station (market prices) and a build system (cost index). Jita/Perimeter is the default primary hub.

## Key skills (manual entry)

Industry, Mass Production, Advanced Industry, Accounting, Broker Relations, Metallurgy, Science, Research. Skill IDs and keys live in `src/lib/skillFields.ts`. Progression paths are in `src/lib/progression.ts`.

## Minerals (raw materials)

Tritanium (34), Pyerite (35), Mexallon (36), Isogen (37), Nocxium (38), Zydrine (39), Megacyte (40). Supply chain leaves stop at minerals or when no sub-blueprint exists.

## Data sources

| Data | Where |
|------|-------|
| Types, blueprints, skills, stations | SDE JSON in `public/data/` (built by `pnpm run fetch-data` from Fuzzwork CSV) |
| Live prices & history | ESI / Fuzzwork via `src/services/market/` |
| System cost indices | ESI industry endpoints |
| User characters, settings, watchlist | localStorage + optional Google Drive sync |

